<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Enable Two-Factor Authentication</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Enable Two-Factor Authentication</h2>
        <p>Scan the QR code below with your Authenticator app (Google Authenticator, Authy, etc.).</p>

        <div class="qr-container">
            <img src="<%= qrCode %>" alt="QR Code" class="qr-code">
        </div>

        <p>After scanning, enter the 6-digit OTP from your authenticator app.</p>

        <form action="/auth/enable-2fa" method="POST" class="otp-form">
            <label for="otp">Enter OTP:</label>
            <input type="text" name="otp" class="otp-input" required placeholder="Enter OTP">
            <button type="submit" class="btn-primary">Verify & Enable 2FA</button>
        </form>

        <% if (error) { %>
            <p class="error-msg"><%= error %></p>
        <% } %>

        <a href="/dashboard" class="btn-secondary">Back to Dashboard</a>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
